BathSoap<-read.csv("BathSoap.csv")
#Finding brand loyality

# Here, We choose the columns from 23 to 31 from Bathsoap dataset which relate to the brand loyality. Loyality can be measured by finding the maximum value among these rows, highest value obatained from a column indicates that the customer loyality towards a Brand represtning that column and hence customer is loyal to that brand.
r1<-BathSoap[,23:31]
BathSoap$Loyality<-as.numeric(apply(r1,1,which.max))

# 1) i. The data includes customers purchase behaviour.

# Purchase behaviour includes columns like 'Brand Runs','Total Volume','No.of Trans', Value, 'Avg.Price', Promotions(0%, 6%, and other promo),'Loyality'.
data1<-BathSoap[,c(13:16, 19:22,47)]
data1.s<-as.data.frame(scale(data1)) # scaling the data

# Elbow chart is used to estimate the optimal K
fviz_nbclust(data1.s,kmeans,method = "silhouette")

# Choosing the optimal K as 3 and to form 3 clusters
model<-kmeans(data1.s,3,nstart=50)

# Visualizing the clusters
fviz_cluster(model,data1.s)

result<-as.data.frame(cbind(1:nrow(model$centers),model$centers))
result$V1<-as.factor(result$V1)

# Characteristics of the cluster

           alphaLines = 0.3

Description of clusters: In Cluster 1: - Number of transactions are comparatively higher than other two clusters. - Customers Purchasing with 6% promo offers are more. - In this Cluster, purchase are mostly made in price cat (2 & 4) and proposition categories(5, 6, 7, 9, 11 and 15) - More number of Customers who are loyal to brands are mostly in this cluster.

In cluster 2: - Average price of purchase is high in this cluster. - Customers usually in this cluster buy products under other promo offer. - In this Cluster, purchase are mostly made in price cat ‘1’ and proposition categories(8, 10, 12 & 13) - We can observe brand loyal customers in this cluster but they are comparatively less than cluster 1.

In Cluster 3: - Average number of products bought in single transaction are higher. - Average transaction done at different brands is high. - In this Cluster, purchase are mostly made in price cat ‘3’ and proposition category ‘14’. - Customers in this cluster usually purchase products under no promo offer or under other promotional offers. But very less customers purcahsing under 6% promo offer. - In this cluster Brand Loyal customers are very less.
